rentid=31	content=<p>  &nbsp;</p> <p>  then compile and run sample programs contained in the installation package (under OpenNI/Sample and OpenNI/platform/YOURSYSTEM/build/sample)</p> <p>  For Visual Studio user, there are precompiled VS project in OpenNI/platform/Win32/build/sample</p> <p>  <b><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Frequent Error Messages</span></b></p> <p>  <strong>\"Failed to open XML, Error: Unknown USB Device Speed\"</strong></p> <p>  You need to use the power adapter for the Kinect camera when using a regular USB port on a PC</p> <p>  <strong>\"error initializing NITE\"</strong></p> <p>  NITE isn\'t installed properly, make sure you have used the correct license key. When it requests for the license key use the one provided by Primesense : 0KOIk2JeIBYClPWVn'),('2011-09-07 14:24:56','173.75.28.77',1,'ezegarra',NULL,'page_redirect','path=./?qa=31&qa_1=how-to-test-a-kinetic-install#a32'),('2011-09-07 14:24:56','173.75.28.77',1,'ezegarra',NULL,'page_enter','params=qa=31&qa_1=how-to-test-a-kinetic-install	path=/~ezegarra/microprobe/index.php'),('2011-09-07 14:25:14','173.75.28.77',1,'ezegarra',NULL,'page_enter','params=qa=ask&cat=3	path=/~ezegarra/microprobe/index.php'),('2011-09-07 14:25:18','173.75.28.77',1,'ezegarra',NULL,'page_enter','params=qa=ask&cat=3	path=/~ezegarra/microprobe/index.php'),('2011-09-07 14:25:18','173.75.28.77',1,'ezegarra',NULL,'q_post','postid=33	parentid=	title=How to develop Kinect application using recorded Kinect data?	content=	format=	text=	tags=	categoryid=3	notify=1	email='),('2011-09-07 14:25:18','173.75.28.77',1,'ezegarra',NULL,'page_redirect','path=./?qa=33&qa_1=how-develop-kinect-application-using-recorded-kinect-data'),('2011-09-07 14:25:18','173.75.28.77',1,'ezegarra',NULL,'page_enter','params=qa=33&qa_1=how-develop-kinect-application-using-recorded-kinect-data	path=/~ezegarra/microprobe/index.php'),('2011-09-07 14:25:20','173.75.28.77',1,'ezegarra',NULL,'page_enter','params=qa=33&qa_1=how-develop-kinect-a